history.content:
Hi! I’m a recent Berkeley grad and EE UGSI with a passion in teaching.


Last semester, I received numerous private tutoring requests to help students better prepare and understand material for 16b. Many of these students had not taken 16a, and lacked a lot of the fundamental circuit knowledge and intuition required to tackle the first module of 16b.


Before the semester begins, I would like to offer paid private tutoring in small groups (no more than 4-5 people) over Zoom with the goal of summarizing the big concepts of 16a. If there is enough interest, we can continue doing small group tutoring throughout the semester to cover 16b concepts. 


If you are interested, please fill out this short google form:


https://docs.google.com/forms/d/e/1FAIpQLScKyDucEu5QEI5peL9YMgmRbIu4MFf7o7aBCv19Og3aAdz-6g/viewform?usp=sf_link



Go bears and best of luck with the upcoming semester:)
history.subject: Taking 16b without 16a?
